[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":908},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":884,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fvue\u002F2022\u002F12\u002F02\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak\u002F":893},"\u002Fvue\u002F20221202\u002F2131448011\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":867,"date":868,"description":869,"extension":870,"lang":871,"meta":872,"navigation":595,"path":873,"readingMinutes":716,"seo":874,"standalone":875,"stem":876,"tags":877,"tldr":881,"updated":868,"url":882,"__hash__":883},"content\u002Fen\u002FVue\u002Ffix-vue-mustache-flicker-with-v-cloak.md","Fix the Vue Mustache Flicker With v-cloak","8403112114",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":858},"minimark",[11,16,25,32,35,42,45,52,56,67,78,81,87,90,96,102,105,110,117,119,125,236,239,275,278,283,297,300,309,343,354,368,378,382,391,473,827,830,834,838,854],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19,20,24],"p",{},"Sometimes a slow network makes Vue render late, and you briefly see the raw Mustache (",[21,22,23],"code",{},"{{ }}",") syntax on the page. Not a great look — so here's a quick note on how to fix it.",[12,26,28,29,31],{"id":27},"what-causes-the-mustache-to-show","What causes the Mustache (",[21,30,23],{},") to show",[17,33,34],{},"It's actually an interesting issue. Under normal conditions you'd rarely see this:",[17,36,37],{},[38,39],"img",{"alt":40,"src":41},"Mustache showing before Vue instances","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.42.32.png",[17,43,44],{},"What's happening? The main cause is that the network is slow enough that Vue's JavaScript file hasn't finished downloading yet.",[17,46,47,48,51],{},"Normally the HTML file downloads first, so you see the HTML content first. As the browser starts rendering the HTML from top to bottom and hits a ",[21,49,50],{},"\u003Cscript>"," tag, it starts downloading the JavaScript file. Once that file downloads, it starts executing. That's the basic rendering flow.",[12,53,55],{"id":54},"how-to-reproduce-it","How to reproduce it",[17,57,58,59,66],{},"Reproducing this is easy. Here's a ",[60,61,65],"a",{"href":62,"rel":63},"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FPopawrR?editors=1010",[64],"nofollow","CodePen"," sample — try throttling your network speed and watch what happens.",[68,69,77],"iframe",{"height":70,"style":71,"scrolling":72,"title":73,"src":74,"frameBorder":72,"loading":75,"allowTransparency":76,"allowFullScreen":76},300,"width: 100%;","no","Vue3 Composition API","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FPopawrR?default-tab=html%2Cresult","lazy","true","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FPopawrR\">\n  Vue3 Composition API\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,79,80],{},"In Firefox, the throttling option is here:",[17,82,83],{},[38,84],{"alt":85,"src":86},"Network","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.51.19.png",[17,88,89],{},"In the dropdown, pick your network speed:",[17,91,92],{},[38,93],{"alt":94,"src":95},"Speed","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.51.26.png",[17,97,98,99,101],{},"Pick \"2G Good\" or \"3G Good\", reload the CodePen, and you'll see the Mustache (",[21,100,23],{},") flicker.",[17,103,104],{},"Chrome's option is in the same place too:",[17,106,107],{},[38,108],{"alt":85,"src":109},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202022-12-02%2016.53.34.png",[17,111,112,113,116],{},"To fix this, we use Vue's ",[21,114,115],{},"v-cloak"," directive.",[12,118,115],{"id":115},[17,120,121,122,124],{},"The fix is super simple — just add ",[21,123,115],{}," to the tag:",[126,127,132],"pre",{"className":128,"code":129,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-html shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","\u003Cdiv id=\"app\">\n  \u003Cp v-cloak>\n    My name is: {{ myName }}\n  \u003C\u002Fp>\n  \u003Cbr>\n  \u003Cinput type=\"text\" v-model=\"myName\">\n\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n","html","",[21,133,134,161,174,180,190,200,226],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,136,139,143,147,151,154,158],"span",{"class":137,"line":138},"line",1,[135,140,142],{"class":141},"sMAXC","\u003C",[135,144,146],{"class":145},"sKpQp","div",[135,148,150],{"class":149},"sCcAr"," id",[135,152,153],{"class":141},"=",[135,155,157],{"class":156},"sTRMh","\"app\"",[135,159,160],{"class":141},">\n",[135,162,164,167,169,172],{"class":137,"line":163},2,[135,165,166],{"class":141},"  \u003C",[135,168,17],{"class":145},[135,170,171],{"class":149}," v-cloak",[135,173,160],{"class":141},[135,175,177],{"class":137,"line":176},3,[135,178,179],{"class":141},"    My name is: {{ myName }}\n",[135,181,183,186,188],{"class":137,"line":182},4,[135,184,185],{"class":141},"  \u003C\u002F",[135,187,17],{"class":145},[135,189,160],{"class":141},[135,191,193,195,198],{"class":137,"line":192},5,[135,194,166],{"class":141},[135,196,197],{"class":145},"br",[135,199,160],{"class":141},[135,201,203,205,208,211,213,216,219,221,224],{"class":137,"line":202},6,[135,204,166],{"class":141},[135,206,207],{"class":145},"input",[135,209,210],{"class":149}," type",[135,212,153],{"class":141},[135,214,215],{"class":156},"\"text\"",[135,217,218],{"class":149}," v-model",[135,220,153],{"class":141},[135,222,223],{"class":156},"\"myName\"",[135,225,160],{"class":141},[135,227,229,232,234],{"class":137,"line":228},7,[135,230,231],{"class":141},"\u003C\u002F",[135,233,146],{"class":145},[135,235,160],{"class":141},[17,237,238],{},"Then add a little CSS:",[126,240,244],{"className":241,"code":242,"language":243,"meta":131,"style":131},"language-css shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","[v-cloak] {\n  display: none;\n}\n","css",[21,245,246,256,270],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,247,248,251,253],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,249,250],{"class":141},"[",[135,252,115],{"class":149},[135,254,255],{"class":141},"] {\n",[135,257,258,261,264,267],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,259,260],{"class":149},"  display",[135,262,263],{"class":141},": ",[135,265,266],{"class":149},"none",[135,268,269],{"class":141},";\n",[135,271,272],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,273,274],{"class":141},"}\n",[17,276,277],{},"Done.",[68,279,282],{"height":70,"style":71,"scrolling":72,"title":280,"src":281,"frameBorder":72,"loading":75,"allowTransparency":76,"allowFullScreen":76},"v-cloak example","https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fembed\u002FyLERxRY?default-tab=html%2Cresult","\n  See the Pen \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\u002Fpen\u002FyLERxRY\">\n  v-cloak example\u003C\u002Fa> by Ray (\u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\u002Fhsiangfeng\">@hsiangfeng\u003C\u002Fa>)\n  on \u003Ca href=\"https:\u002F\u002Fcodepen.io\">CodePen\u003C\u002Fa>.\n",[17,284,285,286,289,290,292,293,296],{},"But you'll notice this approach is slightly silly — to hide a simple piece of text, you're forced to wrap it in a tag like ",[21,287,288],{},"\u003Cp>",", which makes the HTML uglier. You can actually put ",[21,291,115],{}," directly on ",[21,294,295],{},"#app"," to get the same effect.",[17,298,299],{},"Now you might wonder:",[17,301,302,303,305,306,308],{},"\"Is ",[21,304,115],{}," a Vue directive? Earlier you said the rendering is slow because Vue hasn't loaded yet — so how can ",[21,307,115],{}," even work?\"",[17,310,311,312,315,316,319,320,322,323,326,327,329,330,332,333,335,336,338,339,342],{},"Right — it is a Vue directive. But the underlying mechanism is just CSS's ",[21,313,314],{},"display: none",". That property hides the element on the page. Then you use the CSS selector ",[21,317,318],{},"[v-cloak]"," to target all elements with the ",[21,321,115],{}," attribute and set their ",[21,324,325],{},"display"," to ",[21,328,266],{},". Once Vue finishes loading, it automatically removes ",[21,331,115],{}," and the element becomes visible. So you can call it a Vue directive, but really it's just CSS's ",[21,334,314],{}," doing the work — the attribute just has to be ",[21,337,115],{},", not ",[21,340,341],{},"v-hide"," or something else.",[17,344,345,347,348,353],{},[21,346,115],{}," is also covered in the Vue ",[60,349,352],{"href":350,"rel":351},"https:\u002F\u002Fcn.vuejs.org\u002Fapi\u002Fbuilt-in-directives.html#v-cloak",[64],"official docs",". Here's part of the description:",[355,356,357],"blockquote",{},[17,358,359,360,363,364,367],{},"Used to hide un-compiled template until it is ready.\nWhen using in-DOM templates, there may be a \"flash of un-compiled templates\": the user may see raw mustache tags until the mounted component replaces them with rendered content.\nv-cloak will remain on the element until the associated component instance is mounted. Combined with CSS rules such as ",[21,361,362],{},"[v-cloak] { display: none }",", it can be used to hide the raw templates until the component is ready.\nUntil compile finishes, the ",[21,365,366],{},"\u003Cdiv>"," will not be visible.",[17,369,370,371,374,375,377],{},"If you're wondering whether ",[21,372,373],{},"v-if"," could solve this — no, it can't. ",[21,376,373],{}," also needs Vue to finish loading before it can run.",[12,379,381],{"id":380},"improving-v-cloak","Improving v-cloak",[17,383,384,385,387,388,390],{},"Using ",[21,386,314],{}," for ",[21,389,115],{}," works, but it leaves you with a blank screen — bad UX. You can write a little CSS loader so the user at least sees something while Vue loads. Here's a simple version:",[126,392,394],{"className":128,"code":393,"language":130,"meta":131,"style":131},"\u003Cdiv id=\"app\" v-cloak>\n  My name is: {{ myName }}\n  \u003Cbr>\n  \u003Cinput type=\"text\" v-model=\"myName\">\n\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n\u003Cdiv id=\"loader\">\u003C\u002Fdiv>\n",[21,395,396,412,417,425,445,453],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,397,398,400,402,404,406,408,410],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,399,142],{"class":141},[135,401,146],{"class":145},[135,403,150],{"class":149},[135,405,153],{"class":141},[135,407,157],{"class":156},[135,409,171],{"class":149},[135,411,160],{"class":141},[135,413,414],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,415,416],{"class":141},"  My name is: {{ myName }}\n",[135,418,419,421,423],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,420,166],{"class":141},[135,422,197],{"class":145},[135,424,160],{"class":141},[135,426,427,429,431,433,435,437,439,441,443],{"class":137,"line":182},[135,428,166],{"class":141},[135,430,207],{"class":145},[135,432,210],{"class":149},[135,434,153],{"class":141},[135,436,215],{"class":156},[135,438,218],{"class":149},[135,440,153],{"class":141},[135,442,223],{"class":156},[135,444,160],{"class":141},[135,446,447,449,451],{"class":137,"line":192},[135,448,231],{"class":141},[135,450,146],{"class":145},[135,452,160],{"class":141},[135,454,455,457,459,461,463,466,469,471],{"class":137,"line":202},[135,456,142],{"class":141},[135,458,146],{"class":145},[135,460,150],{"class":149},[135,462,153],{"class":141},[135,464,465],{"class":156},"\"loader\"",[135,467,468],{"class":141},">\u003C\u002F",[135,470,146],{"class":145},[135,472,160],{"class":141},[126,474,476],{"className":241,"code":475,"language":243,"meta":131,"style":131},"[v-cloak] + #loader {\n  position: fixed;\n  top: 0;\n  left: 0;\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n  background: #fff;\n  z-index: 9999;\n}\n\n[v-cloak] + #loader:before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: 50%;\n  left: 50%;\n  width: 50px;\n  height: 50px;\n  border-radius: 50%;\n  border: 3px solid #ccc;\n  border-top-color: #333;\n  animation: spin 1s linear infinite;\n}\n\n@keyframes spin {\n  to {\n    transform: rotate(360deg);\n  }\n}\n",[21,477,478,497,509,521,532,547,560,572,585,590,597,613,626,638,652,665,679,692,706,727,740,763,768,773,785,793,816,822],{"__ignoreMap":131},[135,479,480,482,484,487,491,494],{"class":137,"line":138},[135,481,250],{"class":141},[135,483,115],{"class":149},[135,485,486],{"class":141},"] ",[135,488,490],{"class":489},"sWyjQ","+",[135,492,493],{"class":149}," #loader",[135,495,496],{"class":141}," {\n",[135,498,499,502,504,507],{"class":137,"line":163},[135,500,501],{"class":149},"  position",[135,503,263],{"class":141},[135,505,506],{"class":149},"fixed",[135,508,269],{"class":141},[135,510,511,514,516,519],{"class":137,"line":176},[135,512,513],{"class":149},"  top",[135,515,263],{"class":141},[135,517,518],{"class":149},"0",[135,520,269],{"class":141},[135,522,523,526,528,530],{"class":137,"line":182},[135,524,525],{"class":149},"  left",[135,527,263],{"class":141},[135,529,518],{"class":149},[135,531,269],{"class":141},[135,533,534,537,539,542,545],{"class":137,"line":192},[135,535,536],{"class":149},"  width",[135,538,263],{"class":141},[135,540,541],{"class":149},"100",[135,543,544],{"class":489},"%",[135,546,269],{"class":141},[135,548,549,552,554,556,558],{"class":137,"line":202},[135,550,551],{"class":149},"  height",[135,553,263],{"class":141},[135,555,541],{"class":149},[135,557,544],{"class":489},[135,559,269],{"class":141},[135,561,562,565,567,570],{"class":137,"line":228},[135,563,564],{"class":149},"  background",[135,566,263],{"class":141},[135,568,569],{"class":149},"#fff",[135,571,269],{"class":141},[135,573,575,578,580,583],{"class":137,"line":574},8,[135,576,577],{"class":149},"  z-index",[135,579,263],{"class":141},[135,581,582],{"class":149},"